translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah was walking down the streets of Lethram."
    new "Sarah was walking down the streets of Lethram."

    old "Though the house provided for them in many ways, it seemed still limited in the more basic necessities."
    new "Though the house provided for them in many ways, it seemed still limited in the more basic necessities."

    old "Food. Drink. Lumber for the fireplace."
    new "Food. Drink. Lumber for the fireplace."

    old "Fortunately, the city of Lethram had an abundance of everything and money was no real obstacle, given what Xan had left behind."
    new "Fortunately, the city of Lethram had an abundance of everything and money was no real obstacle, given what Xan had left behind."

    old "Every week, Sarah made her way down to the local market and placed her order slip with one of the general merchants."
    new "Every week, Sarah made her way down to the local market and placed her order slip with one of the general merchants."

    old "Like clockwork, a day later, a cart would resupply them with everything from the list."
    new "Like clockwork, a day later, a cart would resupply them with everything from the list."

    old "It was easy work, perhaps even beneath her as a mage, but the truth was that she liked the excuse."
    new "It was easy work, perhaps even beneath her as a mage, but the truth was that she liked the excuse."

    old "The excuse to get out of the house for a moment. Walk the streets of the city. Feel ordinary, if only for a brief moment."
    new "The excuse to get out of the house for a moment. Walk the streets of the city. Feel ordinary, if only for a brief moment."

    old "Lost in thought, Sarah wandered along her route, when a voice suddenly snapped her out of it."
    new "Lost in thought, Sarah wandered along her route, when a voice suddenly snapped her out of it."

    old "Hey, girlie. Over here."
    new "Hey, girlie. Over here."

    old "Sarah turned towards the voice, though she knew who it was before she even saw him."
    new "Sarah turned towards the voice, though she knew who it was before she even saw him."

    old "She sighed, deeply and loudly."
    new "She sighed, deeply and loudly."

    old "In a city of hundreds-of-thousands of people, from every corner of the world, it was this idiot that she kept running into."
    new "In a city of hundreds-of-thousands of people, from every corner of the world, it was this idiot that she kept running into."

    old "Why the sigh? You're not happy to see me?"
    new "Why the sigh? You're not happy to see me?"

    old "He had that familiar arrogant grin on his face."
    new "He had that familiar arrogant grin on his face."

    old "Sarah walked up towards him. Part of her wanted to ignore him, but she knew no good would come from that."
    new "Sarah walked up towards him. Part of her wanted to ignore him, but she knew no good would come from that."

    old "Then again, little good ever seemed to come from engaging with him either."
    new "Then again, little good ever seemed to come from engaging with him either."

    old "Alaric..."
    new "Alaric..."

    old "Free city, ain't it? I can go and not go where I want."
    new "Free city, ain't it? I can go and not go where I want."

    old "We can ask the guards how they feel about that."
    new "We can ask the guards how they feel about that."

    old "Alaric's smile dropped."
    new "Alaric's smile dropped."

    old "Now why would we go and ruin a great day like this, by doin somethin stupid like that?"
    new "Now why would we go and ruin a great day like this, by doin somethin stupid like that?"

    old "Sarah kept meeting his gaze."
    new "Sarah kept meeting his gaze."

    old "Whatever. I have work to do, so if you're done bothering me, I'll be on my way."
    new "Whatever. I have work to do, so if you're done bothering me, I'll be on my way."

    old "Sarah tried to turn, but before she could, he grabbed her shoulder."
    new "Sarah tried to turn, but before she could, he grabbed her shoulder."

    old "Now, hang on a sec, I barely got a word out."
    new "Now, hang on a sec, I barely got a word out."

    old "Spit out then."
    new "Spit out then."

    old "And you better watch what you're saying too, before you go asking me something stupid."
    new "And you better watch what you're saying too, before you go asking me something stupid."

    old "Me? A dishonorable proposal? I wouldn't dare."
    new "Me? A dishonorable proposal? I wouldn't dare."

    old "Alaric looked from side to side."
    new "Alaric looked from side to side."

    old "No, look girlie, while I'd love to take you out back to the alley and remind you what's what-"
    new "No, look girlie, while I'd love to take you out back to the alley and remind you what's what-"

    old "Watch it."
    new "Watch it."

    old "The truth is that I actually got a real problem I wanted to discuss with you."
    new "The truth is that I actually got a real problem I wanted to discuss with you."

    old "She suddenly saw real worry on his face."
    new "She suddenly saw real worry on his face."

    old "She'd never seen that expression on his face before."
    new "She'd never seen that expression on his face before."

    old "Sarah's voice became genuinely curious."
    new "Sarah's voice became genuinely curious."

    old "So...a while back I helped a couple of businessmen out. They had a package that they wanted to sell, and I offered to take it off their hands."
    new "So...a while back I helped a couple of businessmen out. They had a package that they wanted to sell, and I offered to take it off their hands."

    old "Now, as for the contents of the package...well it is what it is, I don't think that's very relevant."
    new "Now, as for the contents of the package...well it is what it is, I don't think that's very relevant."

    old "Drugs. Stolen goods. Sarah could imagine a whole host of it things. Given that it was Alaric, none of it good."
    new "Drugs. Stolen goods. Sarah could imagine a whole host of it things. Given that it was Alaric, none of it good."

    old "Anyway, the deal was simple."
    new "Anyway, the deal was simple."

    old "I take the stuff off their hands, I go and sell it for em, then I pay them off and pocket the difference."
    new "I take the stuff off their hands, I go and sell it for em, then I pay them off and pocket the difference."

    old "Honest work, really."
    new "Honest work, really."

    old "The only honest work you'll ever do is if they catch you and put you in jail."
    new "The only honest work you'll ever do is if they catch you and put you in jail."

    old "Alaric smirked."
    new "Alaric smirked."

    old "Cute."
    new "Cute."

    old "Anyway, long story short...package is gone and they're knocking."
    new "Anyway, long story short...package is gone and they're knocking."

    old "And the money?"
    new "And the money?"

    old "Well, like I said, package was gone so I never made so much as a dime."
    new "Well, like I said, package was gone so I never made so much as a dime."

    old "Now they're askin for their package back or their money, neither of which I got."
    new "Now they're askin for their package back or their money, neither of which I got."

    old "He leaned in closer."
    new "He leaned in closer."

    old "And these are...well I know you don't like me much, but these are some real bad fuckin guys."
    new "And these are...well I know you don't like me much, but these are some real bad fuckin guys."

    old "So you lost their package, and now you're in trouble."
    new "So you lost their package, and now you're in trouble."

    old "Can't you just tell them that? Offer to pay them back later?"
    new "Can't you just tell them that? Offer to pay them back later?"

    old "You don't swim in the waters that I swim in, girlie. These gentlemen ain't takin a promise, if you get my drift."
    new "You don't swim in the waters that I swim in, girlie. These gentlemen ain't takin a promise, if you get my drift."

    old "So you don't have money either?"
    new "So you don't have money either?"

    old "Not the kind they're lookin for. And I can't make so much any time soon."
    new "Not the kind they're lookin for. And I can't make so much any time soon."

    old "For a moment, he paused. Then he continued."
    new "For a moment, he paused. Then he continued."

    old "So I was thinkin if maybe...I could hide out for a bit maybe? Let this all blow over?"
    new "So I was thinkin if maybe...I could hide out for a bit maybe? Let this all blow over?"

    old "Her house? Never."
    new "Her house? Never."

    old "Not in a million fucking years are you going anywhere near my house."
    new "Not in a million fucking years are you going anywhere near my house."

    old "Hell, I'll promise you first thing I do when I get home is put a ward on the door that will burn you if you even try."
    new "Hell, I'll promise you first thing I do when I get home is put a ward on the door that will burn you if you even try."

    old "Sarah didn't know a spell like that, but she also knew Alaric couldn't tell if she was bluffing."
    new "Sarah didn't know a spell like that, but she also knew Alaric couldn't tell if she was bluffing."

    old "The look on his face was one of genuine fear."
    new "The look on his face was one of genuine fear."

    old "Alaric was ruthless, a creature raised on the streets of Lethram, but he understood his own world."
    new "Alaric was ruthless, a creature raised on the streets of Lethram, but he understood his own world."

    old "The world of magic was strange to him, and like most people, he was unsettled by it and preferred not to think about it."
    new "The world of magic was strange to him, and like most people, he was unsettled by it and preferred not to think about it."

    old "Fine, whatever. But you still gotta help me! These guys ain't playin around."
    new "Fine, whatever. But you still gotta help me! These guys ain't playin around."

    old "Why in the name of all the Gods would I help you?"
    new "Why in the name of all the Gods would I help you?"

    old "She saw his face sink."
    new "She saw his face sink."

    old "Because...I don't know."
    new "Because...I don't know."

    old "His voice dropped off."
    new "His voice dropped off."

    old "You're not exactly the first person I thought about askin, but look...I don't got nobody."
    new "You're not exactly the first person I thought about askin, but look...I don't got nobody."

    old "And these guys...they're really not messin around. They're gonna come find me any day now when they do..."
    new "And these guys...they're really not messin around. They're gonna come find me any day now when they do..."

    old "Sarah...they're gonna kill me."
    new "Sarah...they're gonna kill me."

    old "There was none of his smirking. His arrogance. He seemed genuinely desperate."
    new "There was none of his smirking. His arrogance. He seemed genuinely desperate."

    old "Sarah stomped her feet on the pavement and sighed out her frustration."
    new "Sarah stomped her feet on the pavement and sighed out her frustration."

    old "Is that a yes?"
    new "Is that a yes?"

    old "Whatever! It's a very relucant yes. I'll help you talk to these guys, make sure nothing happens to you."
    new "Whatever! It's a very relucant yes. I'll help you talk to these guys, make sure nothing happens to you."

    old "That's...you're amazing! I knew you were a good person."
    new "That's...you're amazing! I knew you were a good person."

    old "Good person?"
    new "Good person?"

    old "Maybe I just take pity on the pitiable."
    new "Maybe I just take pity on the pitiable."

    old "Well, whatever way you wanna spin it, I ain't gonna turn down your help."
    new "Well, whatever way you wanna spin it, I ain't gonna turn down your help."

    old "So, who are these people anyway?"
    new "So, who are these people anyway?"

    old "They're called the Romanov Twins."
    new "They're called the Romanov Twins."

    old "Brothers?"
    new "Brothers?"

    old "Nah. Not even related. And their names ain't even Romanov. Fuck if I know how some people earn their nicknames."
    new "Nah. Not even related. And their names ain't even Romanov. Fuck if I know how some people earn their nicknames."

    old "But they look alike enough, so maybe that's it."
    new "But they look alike enough, so maybe that's it."

    old "Focus. I don't care how anybody earned their nickname."
    new "Focus. I don't care how anybody earned their nickname."

    old "Where can we find these guys?"
    new "Where can we find these guys?"

    old "Well, tell you the truth...they'll find us."
    new "Well, tell you the truth...they'll find us."

    old "They were gonna be visitin me at my home today."
    new "They were gonna be visitin me at my home today."

    old "Your home?"
    new "Your home?"

    old "Sarah was surprised to learn that someone like Alaric had a home."
    new "Sarah was surprised to learn that someone like Alaric had a home."

    old "Well...not a home exactly."
    new "Well...not a home exactly."

    old "A block of buildings in the cannery section burned down a few years back."
    new "A block of buildings in the cannery section burned down a few years back."

    old "Most of it is still smoked out ruin, but there are a few appartments that are officially unlivable."
    new "Most of it is still smoked out ruin, but there are a few appartments that are officially unlivable."

    old "Unlivable?"
    new "Unlivable?"

    old "Yeah, on paper. In truth, they make decent homes and nobody charges you nothin for it."
    new "Yeah, on paper. In truth, they make decent homes and nobody charges you nothin for it."

    old "If you can stand the rats, it ain't all bad."
    new "If you can stand the rats, it ain't all bad."

    old "This explanation made a lot more sense for the kind of person she thought he was."
    new "This explanation made a lot more sense for the kind of person she thought he was."

    old "Still, some part of her couldn't help but feel empathy, even for someone like him."
    new "Still, some part of her couldn't help but feel empathy, even for someone like him."

    old "For all his crimes and schemes, he didn't even really seem to benefit from much of it."
    new "For all his crimes and schemes, he didn't even really seem to benefit from much of it."

    old "Robbing, stealing. And still he lived in squalor."
    new "Robbing, stealing. And still he lived in squalor."

    old "Sarah shook her head. Focus. Don't feel sorry for him."
    new "Sarah shook her head. Focus. Don't feel sorry for him."

    old "Alright, so if we got to your place...they should show up there, right?"
    new "Alright, so if we got to your place...they should show up there, right?"

    old "And with a mage on my side, these fuckers will think twice about messin with me again."
    new "And with a mage on my side, these fuckers will think twice about messin with me again."

    old "Fine. I'll help you out but I'm not going to hurt anyone. Not unless I have to, I mean."
    new "Fine. I'll help you out but I'm not going to hurt anyone. Not unless I have to, I mean."

    old "I'll scare them just fine, but I don't need any trouble with the law. I think you got plenty for the both of us."
    new "I'll scare them just fine, but I don't need any trouble with the law. I think you got plenty for the both of us."

    old "Sure, sure. Scare em good and I'll owe you."
    new "Sure, sure. Scare em good and I'll owe you."

    old "Owe me? What favors are you gonna do for me?"
    new "Owe me? What favors are you gonna do for me?"

    old "Alaric winked at her."
    new "Alaric winked at her."

    old "I got some skills a lady might appreciate."
    new "I got some skills a lady might appreciate."

    old "Lets just get this over with, alright?"
    new "Lets just get this over with, alright?"

    old "Together, the two began to walk. Alaric served as her guide in this part of the city."
    new "Together, the two began to walk. Alaric served as her guide in this part of the city."

    old "Sarah looked around as she slowly saw the buildings turn for the worse."
    new "Sarah looked around as she slowly saw the buildings turn for the worse."

    old "Though she'd lived in Lethram for a good few years by now, the truth was that her life played out in predictable patterns."
    new "Though she'd lived in Lethram for a good few years by now, the truth was that her life played out in predictable patterns."

    old "She'd go to the market. To the docks on occasion. Then back to her home."
    new "She'd go to the market. To the docks on occasion. Then back to her home."

    old "She didn't wander the streets at random, and without an excuse, she'd never had a reason to come to this part of town before."
    new "She didn't wander the streets at random, and without an excuse, she'd never had a reason to come to this part of town before."

    old "Who said I'm worried?"
    new "Who said I'm worried?"

    old "I can see it all on your face. Nobody here is gonna fuck with you. Not when you're with me at least."
    new "I can see it all on your face. Nobody here is gonna fuck with you. Not when you're with me at least."

    old "I can do magic, remember? Nothing here that scares me."
    new "I can do magic, remember? Nothing here that scares me."

    old "And still you look like you seen a ghost."
    new "And still you look like you seen a ghost."

    old "Maybe you just not used to places like this. More at home in a mansion, huh?"
    new "Maybe you just not used to places like this. More at home in a mansion, huh?"

    old "A mansion? What makes you say that."
    new "A mansion? What makes you say that."

    old "First time I met you, you still had a fancy dress. They don't make those for ordinary girls."
    new "First time I met you, you still had a fancy dress. They don't make those for ordinary girls."

    old "And everything about you screams noble girl. Or at the very least a rich daddy."
    new "And everything about you screams noble girl. Or at the very least a rich daddy."

    old "Well, everything about you, except for how you suck dick. You do that like a proper street girl."
    new "Well, everything about you, except for how you suck dick. You do that like a proper street girl."

    old "Sarah looked at him, eyes full of anger."
    new "Sarah looked at him, eyes full of anger."

    old "Didn't I tell you to watch it?"
    new "Didn't I tell you to watch it?"

    old "Just joking. That's how I relieve stress."
    new "Just joking. That's how I relieve stress."

    old "Stress, huh? Which of us is scared?"
    new "Stress, huh? Which of us is scared?"

    old "Well, I ain't the one that can shoot fire from my hands. If this goes sideways, it's my ass that's on the line."
    new "Well, I ain't the one that can shoot fire from my hands. If this goes sideways, it's my ass that's on the line."

    old "They continued walking."
    new "They continued walking."

    old "Weaving between narrow alleys and high buildings, it was almost like the sun was being drowned out."
    new "Weaving between narrow alleys and high buildings, it was almost like the sun was being drowned out."

    old "These places lived in a perpetual shade, Sarah realized as she followed Alaric."
    new "These places lived in a perpetual shade, Sarah realized as she followed Alaric."

    old "For his part, he seemed to have a natural sense of direction in this maze."
    new "For his part, he seemed to have a natural sense of direction in this maze."

    old "It made sense, Sarah thought. He'd spend his life navigating these alleys. Of course he knew them like the back of his hand."
    new "It made sense, Sarah thought. He'd spend his life navigating these alleys. Of course he knew them like the back of his hand."

    old "Finally, they made their way through the partially burned down cannery housing blocks."
    new "Finally, they made their way through the partially burned down cannery housing blocks."

    old "Sarah followed Alaric as he pushed open a door."
    new "Sarah followed Alaric as he pushed open a door."

    old "Inside, like he had promised, Sarah found a livable room."
    new "Inside, like he had promised, Sarah found a livable room."

    old "That was about all that she could say for it. No luxury. Nothing that made it seem like there was any personal touch to it."
    new "That was about all that she could say for it. No luxury. Nothing that made it seem like there was any personal touch to it."

    old "A room. Efficient. Effective."
    new "A room. Efficient. Effective."

    old "Depressing."
    new "Depressing."

    old "You live here like this?"
    new "You live here like this?"

    old "I told you, it's cheap. About all I care about."
    new "I told you, it's cheap. About all I care about."

    old "Yeah I know, but still..."
    new "Yeah I know, but still..."

    old "What? You don't like what I did with the place?"
    new "What? You don't like what I did with the place?"

    old "You didn't do anything with the place. No pictures. No personal belongings. This might as well be anyone else's house."
    new "You didn't do anything with the place. No pictures. No personal belongings. This might as well be anyone else's house."

    old "She saw an odd look on Alaric's face."
    new "She saw an odd look on Alaric's face."

    old "Could it really be, she thought. Shame?"
    new "Could it really be, she thought. Shame?"

    old "I'm sorry. I didn't mean anything by it."
    new "I'm sorry. I didn't mean anything by it."

    old "Well, fuck me that I don't got a woman's touch to liven up the place."
    new "Well, fuck me that I don't got a woman's touch to liven up the place."

    old "Not a lot of women lined up to get hitched to a fucker like me."
    new "Not a lot of women lined up to get hitched to a fucker like me."

    old "Sarah pressed her fingers together."
    new "Sarah pressed her fingers together."

    old "Ooh poor Alaric."
    new "Ooh poor Alaric."

    old "Nobody wants to get married to a criminal."
    new "Nobody wants to get married to a criminal."

    old "Can you hear that? It's the world's smallest violin, playing just for you."
    new "Can you hear that? It's the world's smallest violin, playing just for you."

    old "His face darkened."
    new "His face darkened."

    old "Fuck you."
    new "Fuck you."

    old "Hey now, you still need my help. Better be nice to me."
    new "Hey now, you still need my help. Better be nice to me."

    old "Ooh, I'll promise I'll be real nice to you when this is over."
    new "Ooh, I'll promise I'll be real nice to you when this is over."

    old "Sarah wasn't sure whether to take that as a promise or a threat. Maybe a bit of each."
    new "Sarah wasn't sure whether to take that as a promise or a threat. Maybe a bit of each."

    old "Still, she wasn't too worried. He didn't pose a real danger to her. Not anymore. Not with her magic."
    new "Still, she wasn't too worried. He didn't pose a real danger to her. Not anymore. Not with her magic."

    old "Sarah leaned up against one of the walls."
    new "Sarah leaned up against one of the walls."

    old "So...now what?"
    new "So...now what?"

    old "When are these idiots gonna show up?"
    new "When are these idiots gonna show up?"

    old "Beats me. They said I had to have the money today, but criminals aren't exactly known for keeping tight schedules."
    new "Beats me. They said I had to have the money today, but criminals aren't exactly known for keeping tight schedules."

    old "So what...we just wait around here?"
    new "So what...we just wait around here?"

    old "Got a better idea?"
    new "Got a better idea?"

    old "Fine. But I'm leaving after midnight. Even if they do come and kill you, a girl needs her sleep."
    new "Fine. But I'm leaving after midnight. Even if they do come and kill you, a girl needs her sleep."

    old "Alaric chuckled."
    new "Alaric chuckled."

    old "Fuck, if they ain't here by midnight, I might off myself."
    new "Fuck, if they ain't here by midnight, I might off myself."

    old "Sarah tapped her shoes against the floor. Boredom was already setting in."
    new "Sarah tapped her shoes against the floor. Boredom was already setting in."

    old "Soooooo..."
    new "Soooooo..."

    old "Anything to do until then? I'd say count the minutes on the clock, but you don't even own a clock."
    new "Anything to do until then? I'd say count the minutes on the clock, but you don't even own a clock."

    old "I could fuck your brains out on this bed. That should kill some time."
    new "I could fuck your brains out on this bed. That should kill some time."

    old "Tempting offer, but I think I'll pass."
    new "Tempting offer, but I think I'll pass."

    old "We wouldn't want to be caught with our pants down...literally."
    new "We wouldn't want to be caught with our pants down...literally."

    old "I guess I got a deck of cards here."
    new "I guess I got a deck of cards here."

    old "Alaric fumbled around in one of the drawers next to the bed."
    new "Alaric fumbled around in one of the drawers next to the bed."

    old "Triumphantly, he pulled a deck of cards out."
    new "Triumphantly, he pulled a deck of cards out."

    old "He scratched his chin, as if in deep thought."
    new "He scratched his chin, as if in deep thought."

    old "Do you know how to play Lethram Fasthand?"
    new "Do you know how to play Lethram Fasthand?"

    old "I'm just an uptight rich girl, remember? They don't teach us nothing about card games."
    new "I'm just an uptight rich girl, remember? They don't teach us nothing about card games."

    old "Alaric smiled back at her."
    new "Alaric smiled back at her."

    old "Well, I'll teach you. And maybe we can get you to unwind while we're at it."
    new "Well, I'll teach you. And maybe we can get you to unwind while we're at it."

    old "Sarah sat down on the bed at the opposite end."
    new "Sarah sat down on the bed at the opposite end."

    old "She watched as Alaric began to deal cards, throwing some towards himself, some to her."
    new "She watched as Alaric began to deal cards, throwing some towards himself, some to her."

    old "Five cards to each hand, dealt from the top of the deck."
    new "Five cards to each hand, dealt from the top of the deck."

    old "Three cards to the center, shared between players."
    new "Three cards to the center, shared between players."

    old "Step-by-step, Alric took her through the rules of Lethram Fasthand."
    new "Step-by-step, Alric took her through the rules of Lethram Fasthand."

    old "A mixture of chance, odds, bluffing. Half the game was the cards. The other half reading the player opposite of you."
    new "A mixture of chance, odds, bluffing. Half the game was the cards. The other half reading the player opposite of you."

    old "What are we betting anyway?"
    new "What are we betting anyway?"

    old "Betting?"
    new "Betting?"

    old "Yeah, can't play Fasthand without a proper bet."
    new "Yeah, can't play Fasthand without a proper bet."

    old "Well, nice as your furniture is, I don't think I really wanna win anything in here. Probably has termites."
    new "Well, nice as your furniture is, I don't think I really wanna win anything in here. Probably has termites."

    old "Sure, how about a question."
    new "Sure, how about a question."

    old "A question?"
    new "A question?"

    old "Yeah, winner gets to pose the other a question. Whichever they like. Loser has to answer honestly."
    new "Yeah, winner gets to pose the other a question. Whichever they like. Loser has to answer honestly."

    old "Sure, we can bet that."
    new "Sure, we can bet that."

    old "After a few quick rounds to learn the rules, they began to play for real."
    new "After a few quick rounds to learn the rules, they began to play for real."

    old "Sarah was surprised to find herself enjoying it."
    new "Sarah was surprised to find herself enjoying it."

    old "Staring deep into Alaric's face, she did her best to read him."
    new "Staring deep into Alaric's face, she did her best to read him."

    old "He was never the easiest person to read, but when playing the game, he seemed especially slippery."
    new "He was never the easiest person to read, but when playing the game, he seemed especially slippery."

